This paper is primarily concerned with the convergence of a dynamic for two-player zero-sum games, which falls under the field of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the rate of convergence and assumptions about the structure of the game, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses mathematical tools such as smoothness and optimization, which are relevant to the fields of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
